"Here we belong, fighting for survival.  We've come to be the rulers of you all."  -- Freddie Mercury


Valdayana D`Varr placed her hand on the ranger's forehead and chanted an arcane incantation.  Suddenly she felt a searing heat course through her body.  She saw through the ranger's eyes the events that transpired.


The Burning Lands of Doomfire. (Plane of Fire)

"So you are to be a vessel for my power?  Fennin Ro's challenge echoed through the ranger's thoughts, a seeming impossibility since his corporeal form was lying in a heap on the ground.  

"Take the dancing flame.  In time you will be called upon to prevent a headlong charge into the total oblivion of reality."

Confused, Millikin looked around.  "What?..."  She looked around, half expecting to see the fiery countenance of the god of fire.  But through the haze borne of perpetual flame and lava, Millikin's gaze focused on Elyda.  The fair haired Feir`Dal druid was making her way towards the ranger.  The two wood elves seemed similiar to each other at first glance.  Both wore armor that resembled a mix of chain and leather and both served Tunare on a level that transcended 
divine levels and delved into the natural order of existence.  But where Millikin relied primarily on her physical prowess as her source of power and used magic secondarily, Elyda was more attuned towards matters mystical and personally shunned the marital aspects of combat as a druid.  On the field of battle, Elyda was often seen wielding a scimitar, allegedly blessed by the god Mithaniel Marr himself, but her cheerful demeanor seemed ill-suited to commanding an organized force into open combat against an elemental god.  However, appearances could be deceiving and the fact that Fennin Ro's body was currently smoldering before his very throne was stark testament to the druid's leadership abilities.

"Here."  Elyda tossed a small dark object towards the ranger who reflexively reached up to catch it with her left hand.  Millikin looked down at the object in her hand.  A small translucent orb contained a small fire flickered within its glassy housing.  She could feel the heat emanating within the globe.  Millikin looked up quizzically at the druid.

"The elemental who left them said we will need them later."  Elyda explained.  "And one of the elders in Knowledge said he could help if we gather the essences of the gods together."

Millikin nodded slightly, still remembering what she had just heard.


